defaultDr David Barrettdefault:default I could not really comment on whether they are accurate or not; it is a very difficult thing to measure, and it is also very difficult to measure how much losses are according to corruption as opposed to fraud. Anyone who is involved in corruption and fraud has an interest in covering it up, and often the power to do so, so it is a difficult thing to measure. I would say that it is very important to make these efforts to measure it at a national level and to have a body with the responsibility for trying to collect that data, and to be able to hence pick out from that what the trends are, and where the risk areas are. 
